body:
With verilator 5.0.34, I am getting an error with the following test code:

    module test #(
        parameter LEN = 4,
        parameter LST[LEN] = '{LEN{0}}
    )();

    endmodule

    module top();

    parameter LEN = 8;

    test #(
        .LEN(LEN),
        .LST('{LEN{0}})
    )
    inst1();

    test #(
        .LEN(LEN)
    )
    inst2();

    endmodule

The error is:

    %Error: bug.sv:15:14: Assignment pattern with too many elements
                        : ... note: In instance 'top'
       15 |         .LST('{LEN{0}})
          |              ^~
    %Error: bug.sv:4:30: Assignment pattern with too many elements
                       : ... note: In instance 'top.inst2'
        4 |         parameter LST[LEN] = '{LEN{0}}
          |                              ^~
    %Error: Exiting due to 2 error(s)

The error does not appear if I do not change the value of the LEN parameter.

It seems that the parameter override isn't getting applied to the type correctly.
